On its Twitter account, the Presidency says it has received a request from the White House for a teleconference between Zuma and Trump. JOHANNESBURG The Presidency has confirmed that President Jacob Zuma is expecting a call from United States (US) President Donald Trump sometime on Monday. On its Twitter account, the Presidency says it has received a request from the White House for a teleconference between Zuma and Trump.The Presidency confirms a request from the White House for a telecon between President Zuma and President Trump this afternoon, 13/2/17Trump was elected president of the US last November.He was officially sworn in last month.(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)